description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an enthusiastic and motivated person to join the Acute Paediatrics team at Ysbyty Gwynedd, Bangor as a Ward Clerk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for answering the telephone, dealing with enquiries, admitting, transferring and discharge of patients on the patient administration system, filing and making up set of notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will poses good communication and customer service skills, they will be organised and will have the ability to prioritise their workload and meet deadlines. The successful applicant will be computer literate and previous experience within the NHS environment could be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work using your own initiative, managing your own workload as well as being part of the ward team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The working hours will be;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Evenings 15:30- 20:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekends and Bank holidays 10:00-18:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be on a rota basis. As and when required the post holder would be expected to cover Leave or absences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is essential for this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glesni Jordan, Admin Manager&lt;br /&gt;glesni.jordan@wales.nhs.uk&lt;br /&gt;01248 384617&lt;/p&gt;
